# Alembic Migration Guide

This folder contains database migration configuration for the project.

## Files

- `env.py` — Alembic runtime environment, wired to SQLAlchemy metadata in `app.models`.
- `script.py.mako` — Template used to generate new migration files.
- `versions/` — Versioned migration scripts.

## Common commands

Run from the repository root.

### 1) Check current revision

```bash
uv run alembic current
```

### 2) Apply pending migrations

```bash
uv run alembic upgrade head
```

### 3) Create a new migration after model changes

```bash
uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"
uv run alembic upgrade head
```

### 4) Existing database bootstrap (already has tables)

If your database tables were created before Alembic, stamp the revision first:

```bash
uv run alembic stamp head
```

This marks the schema as managed at the current head without recreating existing tables.

## Notes

- Production deployments should use PostgreSQL via `DATABASE_URL`.
- Keep migrations forward-only where possible; test migrations in staging before production.
